q1 -> For each month (based on start_date), calculate the total number of subscriptions started, the total expected revenue (subscription duration in months × monthly price), and the average expected revenue per subscription. Round averages to 2 decimal places. Order by month ascending.


sol 1-> WITH differences     AS (SELECT user_id,                plan_type,                start_date,                TIMESTAMPDIFF(MONTH, start_date, end_date)  AS DIFFERENCE         FROM   subscriptions),     differences_2     AS (SELECT D.user_id,                D.plan_type,                D.start_date,                D.difference * P.monthly_price AS EXPECTED         FROM   differences D                JOIN plan_pricing P                  ON D.plan_type = P.plan_type)SELECT Date_format(D.start_date, '%Y-%M'),       Count(D.plan_type),       Sum(EXPECTED)                                AS TOTAL_EXPECTED_REVENUE,       Round(Sum(EXPECTED) / Count(D.plan_type), 2) AS       AVG_REVENUE_PER_SUBSCRIPTIONFROM   differences_2GROUP  BY Date_format(D.start_date, '%Y-%M') ORDER  BY Date_format(D.start_date, '%Y-%M')
